OL,3,CMum's stories helping non-verbal
OL,4,Cdaughter understand terminal cancer
OL,6,FA mum with terminal cancer has set out
OL,7,Fto create stories to help her non-
OL,8,Fverbal autistic daughter prepare for
OL,9,Flife without her.
OL,11,FKylie Lang, 42, from Brighouse, West
OL,12,FYorkshire, was told she was unlikely
OL,13,Fto survive more than five years after
OL,14,Fbeing diagnosed with breast cancer in
OL,15,F2019.
OL,17,FAfter she was given the news, she
OL,18,Fdiscovered there were no books or
OL,19,Fpamphlets to help her explain her
OL,20,Fheartbreaking situation to her
OL,21,Fdaughter Elsie.
